Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Jason Holder strikes on his very first delivery! An impactful bowling change from Kraigg Brathwaite gets the hosts their first breakthrough! Holder steams from over the wicket and hits the hard length with the angle coming into the right-hander on off. The ball sticks a tad to the surface and then skids a bit low off the deck. Aiden Markram with no foot movement looks to bring his bat down and keep it out but the ball sneaks low past the bat to rattle the off stump. Aiden Markram's dry run continues in red ball and South Africa after a good start are now 43/1.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Excellent awareness at the slip region! They get the big fish in Tony de Zorzi and West Indies will be pumped with this breakthrough. Jomel Warrican floats it fuller and just outside off. Like the other time Tony de Zorzi goes for a reverse sweep but this time he fails to get the perfect connection. Tony gets nicked on the upper part of his bat and the ball loops straight towards the slip fielder, Kavem Hodge who quickly sees the batter and adjusts well behind the ball to take it safely with both hands. After an impressive knock of 78 runs off 145 deliveries Tony de Zorzi has to depart!
Default_Commentary: 49.1: Jomel Warrican to Tony de Zorzi, OUT! c Kavem Hodge b Jomel Warrican.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Keacy Carty YOU BEAUTY! This is pure athlete stuff! Jayden Seales comes sprinting over the wicket and bowls back of a length just outside off.  David Bedingham rocks back and tries to whip it uppishly to clear the deep mid-wicket region but fails to get the elevation. The ball goes flat towards the front right of the fielder patrolling at the deep. Keacy Carty charges towards the ball and dives in front to get the catch into his safe pair of hands. David Bedingham who looked dangerous has to walk back. West Indies are back on track!

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Huge appeal all over the Queen's Park Oval and the Umpire raises his finger this time! Temba Bavuma opted to go upstairs for this one. Jayden Seales fires on a length and pitches it on off. Temba Bavuma tries to work it across the line towards the leg side but misses the connection totally. The ball thumps his pad and the Umpire says yes to the appeal. The replay shows it's three red and Jayden Seales punches the air and keeps his celebration on. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED ONCE AGAIN! This was a screamer from Jomel Warrican! West Indies came back roaring at the end of the Day 2! Keshav Maharaj goes deep into the crease and looks to dab it back but gets the unwanted elevation and the ball loops towards the left of the bowler. Commentary: A big, big shout for caught behind but turned down! Temba Bavuma has a word with the keeper and takes the review with a couple of seconds left on the timer! Commentary: OUT RUN OUT! Excellent effort by Wiaan Mulder! Lackadaisical running by the Windies skipper and he pays the ultimate price. Lungi Ngidi bowls it full and honing in at the stumps, Kraigg Brathwaite gets his weight on the front foot and clips it to the right of mid on. He times it well, resulting in the ball travelling to the fielder quickly and he sets off for a risky single. Wiaan Mulder swoops in, picks it up and hits the stumps at the bowling end. South Africa do not look too interested as the decision is referred upstairs. The replays show that Brathwaite had no part of his bat inside the crease when the bails were dislodged. Moreover, the Windies skipper did not stretch forward fully and plonked his bat instead of sliding it in. Also, the replays show that he ran sideways rather than running in a straight line, resulting in him falling just short of his crease at the bowling end. It turns out that Ngidi had overstepped but it does not affect the run out dismissal in any way. South Africa are delighted as they have finally managed to break this stand. Brathwaite goes for 35. The 61-run stand is broken and West Indies are 114/2. Just as OUT flashed on the big screen, heavens opened up, forcing the umpires to take the players off. It will be TEA on DAY 3!
Default_Commentary: 49.3: Lungi Ngidi to Kraigg Brathwaite, No ball and OUT! run out (Wiaan Mulder).
Howout: run out (Wiaan Mulder)
